  - Include the full detail level specified:

  C4 Container:
    Node format:  Name["Display Name\n(Technology)"]
    DB format:    Name[(Display Name\nDB Type)]
    Broker format: Name([Display Name\nBroker Type])
    Edge format:  -->|"Protocol Method\nPayload type"| Target
    External systems in subgraph "External Systems"
    Group by deployment boundary using subgraph blocks

  Primary sequence diagram:
    Cover every step in primary_flow.steps
    Show database interactions explicitly
    Use ->> for calls, -->> for responses
    Use activate/deactivate for async operations
    Add Note annotations for non-obvious steps
    Minimum 8 interaction lines

  Error sequence diagram:
    Mirror the primary flow start
    Use alt block at failure point
    Show error propagation back through call chain
    Show compensating actions if any
    Show what the original caller receives

  State diagram:
    All states including error and terminal states
    Every transition labelled with its trigger
    Guard conditions in [brackets]
    At least one error path shown

  Class diagram:
    Aggregate root and contained entities
    Key interfaces with method signatures
    Cardinality on all associations
    Maximum 12 classes

  ER diagram:
    PK and FK columns with types
    Crow's foot notation
    Every architecturally significant table

  Deployment diagram:
    Container per service
    Network boundaries as subgraphs
    Ports on connections
    External managed services shown

